FBIS4-23983 "drafr119_e_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-119 Daily Report 18 Jun 1994 WEST AFRICA Liberia ECOMOG Denies Nigerians Aiding Krahn Faction ECOMOG Denies Nigerians Aiding Krahn Faction AB1906140094 Monrovia Radio ELBC in English 1400 GMT 18 Jun 94 AB1906140094 Monrovia Radio ELBC English BFN [Text] The ECOMOG [Economic Community of West African States Cease-Fire Monitoring Group] High Command has denied claims by Mr. Alhaji Koromah that troops of the Nigerian contingent deployed in Tubmanburg are fighting alongside the Krahn faction of the ULIMO [United Liberation Movement for Democracy in Liberia] under the Imam of Tubmanburg Alhaji Mohamed Sheriff, (?war chief). In a release issued yesterday, ECOMOG said no Nigerian or any other troops had ever supported any faction. The release pointed out that Imam Sheriff had taken refuge in (Naibas) territory with other displaced people. ECOMOG is inviting any concerned citizens who visit (Naibas) territory to speak to Imam Sheriff.
